  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a comprehensive observational dataset collected across five clinical-adjacent operating points; the dataset is cited throughout the assessment narrative as satisfying the controlled-experiment requirement for hemolysis benchmarking, given the close correspondence between observed pump operating envelopes and laboratory test conditions. Reviewers are referred to Morrison et al. (2023) for full details of the data acquisition protocol.",
