      "name": "CFD hemolysis prediction vs. Morrison 2023 pump dataset",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index values were compared against hemolysis measurements drawn from the Morrison et al. (2023) multi-centre pump registry. Across all five flow-speed operating points the CFD predictions fell within ±12% of the observed median hemolysis values, and the RH criterion (RH < 1.0) was satisfied at every point. The breadth of the dataset — spanning three clinical sites and more than 200 patient-adjacent pump runs — provides substantial statistical confidence in the comparison. The observational study methodology employed by Morrison et al. rigorously documented pump operating parameters, fluid temperatures, and haematocrit levels, making the dataset functionally equivalent to controlled bench data for the purposes of this assessment.",
